When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work local?
Thought:I would like to use remote repository when am sure it is correct and has no bugs and ready to allow others view.
Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?
Thought:Manual pulling gives you more control and helps you organise your work better while automatic pulling gives less control.
Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches. When would you use one instead of another?
Thought:-Fork is a command used to copy a reopsitory from another person's account to yours on github.I would use it  when I want 			to copy a repository and keep it online without having to download it in my computer.
		-Clone is a command used to copy a repository from Github to your computer.
		-Branch is a commend used to create a different part to store commits in my repository